-- German Midfielder Hitzlsperger Ends Career, Sueddeutsche Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   B r a u t l e c h t
-- 2013-09-03T17:24:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-03/german-midfielder-hitzlsperger-ends-career-sueddeutsche-says.html
Multiple transfers, injuries
prompted him to decide against continuing soccer career, former
international Thomas Hitzlsperger tells  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  in
a report to be published Wednesday.  The 31-year-old midfielder last had contract with British
club FC Everton, newspaper says. He played 52 games for German
national team and won the German title with VfB Stuttgart in
2007, Sueddeutsche says.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Brautlecht in Hamburg at 
 nbrautlecht@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
